 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-ylnl","title":"[Task] Opt 2.3: Add SIMD dot product tests (FP tolerance)","description":"# Task: Add SIMD Dot Product Tests (FP Tolerance)

## Objective

Create tests that verify SIMD dot product produces results within acceptable floating-point tolerance of the scalar version.

## Important: FP Precision Considerations

SIMD reorders floating-point operations, which can cause small differences due to:
- Different addition order (associativity)
- Different rounding at intermediate steps
- Fused multiply-add vs separate multiply/add

Expected difference: ~1e-7 relative error (acceptable for ranking).

## Test Strategy

### 1. Tolerance Test
```rust
#[test]
fn simd_dot_product_matches_scalar_within_tolerance() {
    let a: Vec<f32> = (0..384).map(|i| (i as f32) * 0.001).collect();
    let b: Vec<f32> = (0..384).map(|i| ((384 - i) as f32) * 0.001).collect();

    let scalar = dot_product_scalar(&a, &b);
    let simd = dot_product_simd(&a, &b);

    let rel_error = (scalar - simd).abs() / scalar.abs().max(1e-10);
    assert!(rel_error < 1e-5, 
        "Relative error {} exceeds tolerance. Scalar: {}, SIMD: {}", 
        rel_error, scalar, simd);
}
```

### 2. Random Input Test
```rust
#[test]
fn simd_dot_product_random_inputs() {
    use rand::Rng;
    let mut rng = rand::thread_rng();

    for _ in 0..1000 {
        let a: Vec<f32> = (0..384).map(|_| rng.gen_range(-1.0..1.0)).collect();
        let b: Vec<f32> = (0..384).map(|_| rng.gen_range(-1.0..1.0)).collect();

        let scalar = dot_product_scalar(&a, &b);
        let simd = dot_product_simd(&a, &b);

        let rel_error = (scalar - simd).abs() / scalar.abs().max(1e-10);
        assert!(rel_error < 1e-5, "Failed for random inputs");
    }
}
```

### 3. Edge Cases
```rust
#[test]
fn simd_dot_product_edge_cases() {
    // Empty vectors
    assert_eq!(dot_product_simd(&[], &[]), 0.0);

    // Exactly 8 elements (one SIMD chunk)
    let a = vec![1.0f32; 8];
    let b = vec![1.0f32; 8];
    assert!((dot_product_simd(&a, &b) - 8.0).abs() < 1e-6);

    // 7 elements (only remainder)
    let a = vec![1.0f32; 7];
    let b = vec![1.0f32; 7];
    assert!((dot_product_simd(&a, &b) - 7.0).abs() < 1e-6);

    // 384 elements (48 chunks, no remainder)
    let a = vec![1.0f32; 384];
    let b = vec![1.0f32; 384];
    assert!((dot_product_simd(&a, &b) - 384.0).abs() < 1e-4);

    // Large values
    let a = vec![1e10f32; 384];
    let b = vec![1e-10f32; 384];
    let result = dot_product_simd(&a, &b);
    assert!(result > 0.0 && result < 1e5);
}
```

### 4. Search Result Invariant Test
```rust
#[test]
fn simd_preserves_search_ranking() {
    let index = create_test_index();
    let query = generate_test_query();

    // Search with SIMD disabled
    std::env::set_var("CASS_SIMD_DOT", "0");
    let results_scalar = index.search_top_k(&query, 10, None).unwrap();

    // Search with SIMD enabled
    std::env::remove_var("CASS_SIMD_DOT");
    let results_simd = index.search_top_k(&query, 10, None).unwrap();

    // Same message_ids in same order
    let ids_scalar: Vec<_> = results_scalar.iter().map(|r| r.message_id).collect();
    let ids_simd: Vec<_> = results_simd.iter().map(|r| r.message_id).collect();
    assert_eq!(ids_scalar, ids_simd, "SIMD changed result ranking");
}
```

